<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q36_v7" title="Q36_v7" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>Considera las siguientes afirmaciones sobre dos números reales x e y.</p>
    <div>
      <p>• Dos veces el número x más el número y es igual a 6.</p>
      <p>• Además, tres veces el número x más dos veces el número y es igual a 7.</p>
      <p>¿Cuál es el valor de x que satisface simultáneamente ambas afirmaciones?</p>
    </div>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mfrac>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si x = −5/7, entonces de la primera afirmación se obtiene y = 6 − 2·(−5/7) = 6 + 10/7 = 52/7. Al verificar la segunda afirmación, 3·(−5/7) + 2·(52/7) = −15/7 + 104/7 = 89/7, y 89/7 no es 7. Por lo tanto, ese valor de x no satisface simultáneamente ambas afirmaciones.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Si x = 5, entonces de la primera afirmación se obtiene y = 6 − 2·5 = 6 − 10 = −4. Al verificar la segunda afirmación, 3·5 + 2·(−4) = 15 − 8 = 7. Así, x = 5 satisface simultáneamente ambas afirmaciones.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mfrac><m:mn>19</m:mn><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mfrac>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si x = 19/7, entonces de la primera afirmación se obtiene y = 6 − 2·(19/7) = 42/7 − 38/7 = 4/7. Al verificar la segunda afirmación, 3·(19/7) + 2·(4/7) = 57/7 + 8/7 = 65/7, y 65/7 no es 7. Por lo tanto, ese valor de x no satisface simultáneamente ambas afirmaciones.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si x = −5, entonces de la primera afirmación se obtiene y = 6 − 2·(−5) = 6 + 10 = 16. Al verificar la segunda afirmación, 3·(−5) + 2·16 = −15 + 32 = 17, y 17 no es 7. Por lo tanto, ese valor de x no satisface simultáneamente ambas afirmaciones.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso por sustitución</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Escribir el sistema de ecuaciones</strong></p>
            <p>Del enunciado se obtiene el sistema:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Despejar y en la primera ecuación</strong></p>
            <p>De</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>se obtiene</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Sustituir en la segunda ecuación</strong></p>
            <p>Reemplazamos</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>en</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>y queda:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Resolver la ecuación resultante</strong></p>
            <p>Distribuimos el 2:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Reducimos términos semejantes:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Restamos 12 en ambos lados:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Multiplicamos por −1 en ambos lados:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Verificar el valor obtenido</strong></p>
            <p>Con</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>en la primera ecuación:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Ahora verificamos la segunda ecuación:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>15</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>La verificación es correcta.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>El valor de <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> que satisface simultáneamente ambas afirmaciones es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. La alternativa correcta es la <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>